The paper deals with lower bounds for graph connectivity in a distributed computing model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves combinatorial and information-theoretic techniques, which suggest that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of Combinatorics (cs.CC) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with graph algorithms and lower bounds, which could make it relevant to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
